<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-01-09T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-01-09T10:00:00-05:00" n="78" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d78">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">851.48/119: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Leahy</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Vichy</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-01-09T17:00:00+02:00">January 9,
                                    1941—5 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received January 9—3:38 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>31. Department’s telegram 10, January 6, 6 [<hi rend="italic">8</hi>]
                            p.m. Marshal Petain<note n="5" xml:id="d78fn5">Marshal Henri Philippe
                                Pétain, French Chief of State.</note> and Foreign Minister Flandin
                            assure me this afternoon that the conditions governing the shipment of
                            relief goods are acceptable to the French Government.</p>
                        <p>I shall telegraph in detail tomorrow concerning the interview.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Leahy</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>